{
  "texts": [
    "One possible approach is to consider the atoms in a molecule as nodes and the bonds as edges.",
    "However, alternative mappings are also worth considering.",
    "In standard graph representations, nodes are typically depicted as circles or spheres, while edges are represented as lines.",
    "In molecular graphs, nodes are commonly represented by letters corresponding to the atom type or by points where the bonds intersect, specifically for carbon atoms.",
    "Each node in the graph convolutional layer collects data from its neighbours, representing the regional chemical environment (Bondy and Murty, 1976)."
  ]
}